Came here for lunch a few times. For the poke bowls, you have the option of either rice, brown rice, salad lettuce or zucchini noodles as a base for your bowl and then a protein for the bowl (extra proteins would add some additional cost to the total). The proteins include salmon, tuna, shrimp, chicken, tofu, eel, and some others that I forgot 😅. The other toppings and the sauce are unlimited where u add as much as u want. They put the bowl together right in front of you as u choose the toppings (it's like getting a subway sandwich). This I really like because the process is very quick for my short lunch break. 👍 The seating in the store is very nice too. Very spacious and alot of tables around and in the back. You can come here to do work  since it's not very loud most of the time. Other than that, in my opinion, this location of pokebowl station is better than the one on 7th ave... I feel like the portion of the bowls is bigger here... and more worth the price of the overall bowl. 😬

I'm still eating it as we speak. I been going to the planet fitness on same block for a few months now and been wanting to try this. I don't like cooked fish but I really like sushi, fresh sushi. Not into fishy fish and was afraid that this Chipotle style poke bowl would be weird. I finally tried it tonight and it's delicious. Tuna, spicy tuna, corn, mango, avocado, cilantro, poké special sauce and onion crisps. Fish was very fresh and plenty of toppings and sauces to choose from. They aren't cheap with the amount of sushi they add either. Im down to a few bites and there's still sushi to eat. They have pre made bowls, poke tacos and ice cream and stuff which all look good. I was extremely excited when the storefront sign was put up during its construction. Poké in Brooklyn, at a convenient location by home?! Yes, please! Unfortunately, I never got a chance to try it... until now.  This place is hip, it's modern, it's delicious, it's fresh- all at reasonable prices. I had the rice bowl with spicy tuna and spicy salmon. Great taste. My friend had tuna and chicken, which he really enjoyed. The toppings are free of charge and there are so many options, but the flavors really meld together in the final product. We shared the purple mountain shaved ice bowl for dessert. It is to die for- crunchy from the fruit loops, juicy from the popping boba, tart from the strawberries, and sweet from the taro shaved ice. Again, so many flavors, so many toppings, so many combinations.  I 100% recommend this place. The interior is tastefully decorated, and the food is excellent.

(Translated by Google) The decoration is individual, looks clean and hygienic, the lights are bright and warm, the individual music is played, and the staff are good and polite. For a cup of instant black coffee, the clerk politely told me to wait about four minutes, and recommended an original omelet (the favorite of the beautiful clerk!). Black coffee has a sweet and bitter taste in the mouth. There is a nostalgia for herbal tea. It has the smell of roasted coffee and charcoal. The inconspicuous sourness brings out the subtle change of sweetness and bitterness on the tip of the tongue. It seems to be lightly telling the beauty of bitterness and sweetness. The oil of coffee lubricates the bitter and sweet mouth, with a quiet aftertaste of sweetness. The original egg pie is a sweet egg product. The outer skin is made of iron molds. The softness of the cake is inside, and there is a hint of nostalgia. It is the taste of the staff baking with confidence. This shop is good.  (Original) 装修个性，看上去干净卫生，灯光明亮带暖调，播放个性音乐，店员素质优良有礼貌。 要一杯即磨黑咖啡，店员礼貌地告诉需要等四分钟左右，并推荐一款原味蛋仔饼(美女店员最喜欢的!)。 黑咖啡，入口甘苦味平，有一种凉茶的怀念，有烘焙咖啡烟薰味，炭烧的味道，并不明显的酸味衬托出甘与苦味在舌尖微妙变换，好像在轻诉着苦尽甘来的美好，咖啡的油脂润滑着甘苦的口腔，回味着一丝静悄悄的回甘。 原味蛋仔饼，是甜味蛋制品，外皮是用铁模烤出来的韧性，里面有蛋糕的松软，飘逸着一缕乡愁，是店员用自信烤制出来的味道。 这店不错。
